    			(l, l (mod p)),
    where l runs through prime divisors of the prime-to-p-part of Norm(T), i.e.,

            Norm(T)' = \frac{Norm(T)}{p^{ord_p(Norm(T)}}.

    and Norm(a1)' = Norm(T)'.

    verified this for 5 \leq p \leq 300.
